<Author>LarryWastoday
<Content>Good value for money The hotel was great value for money. OK, it could do with a bit of an update but the room was very spacious and had all the comforts you would expect plus some more (a sofa, for example). The rate we paid (the cheapest for this hotel), included parking (guarded, in the building itself) and a good cooked breakfast.The location is quite good too: a 5-10 minute walk from the centre (Avenida Juarez and Plaza de la Solaridad), 5-10 minute walk to the closest Metro station and a 20-25 minute walk from the Zocalo (or take the Metro). The road the hotel is in is a little rundown but feels perfectly safe.Most of the staff speak little or no English and this may account for some of the previous negative reviews. We found the staff polite and reasonable.On balance, better than expected. 
