<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>not the friendliest staff The hotel was nice. Rooms were spacious. Terrible view of a parking lot. No nice restaraunts nearby.Most of all, the staff was not the friendliest. Everytime I would ask a question they looked at me as if I were stupid. And I spoke to them in spanish!!! Second, several times I cashed american dollars into mexican pesos....and found out later that they were not giving me the correct exchange amount. For every american $20.00 I should have received $222.20pesos..which is $22.20 american dollars. My friend and I must have exchanged at least $200.00 for mexican pesos! I haven't calculated exactly how much they shorted me..but i'm sure we left them a nice chunk of change for them to take home and we didn't even know it! The whole staff is very dishonest! BEWARE to anyone who stays at this Best Western, make sure they know that you know what the exchange value is for every american dollar! And if you plan to make reservations inside the hotel for a tour of the city make sure you don't get ripped off like we did. We paid the man $150.00 american dollars and he pulls up in his 1982 4-door oldsmobile (falling apart) and asks us if we're ready to go! We thought we were going in a tour bus! On the way back from the Pyramids his car starts smoking from the engine and breaks down in the middle of the highway! We were stuck out there for atleast 2 hours. If you're gonna reserve a tour make sure you are going in an actual tour bus with an actual tour guide. The tour is not worth $150.00!!!! We should of paid him $60.00 for all three of us! BE VERY CAUTIOUS!!!!!!!! 
