<Author>cat lips
<Content>a mixed bag The hotel itself is very nice. The lobby and bedrooms are very clean and modern. The restaurant is reasonably priced and the food is more than adequate. The hotel's location is not the best because the area is mostly commercial, so in the evenings there is not much to see and there are very few restaurants in the area.The biggest disappointment was the hotel staff. Some of the front desk personnel were not nice at all. Also, we were told that if we called the hotel while we were out site seeing, the hotel would send a reliable taxi to our location to return us to the hotel. However, when we called the hotel, the front desk said that the hotel could not call a taxi for us. Hence, we were forced to take public transportation during rush hour.The hotel needs to be more responsive to its guests. 
